#12 0x00000000 in ?? ()
```

Is there anything wrong with my code? Why would code crash in a thread that works fine in the main thread and only uses objects that are local to the function and moreover declared thread_local (not that it changes anything about the crash)?

Edit: Just realized that it crashes in the destructor of object_detector instead of operator() in my debug build as reflected by the stack trace. Still, it doesn't crash in the main thread.

Platform: Windows 8
Compiler: MinGW
dlib version: 19.2
Build options: -D__GNUWIN32__ -Wall -std=c++11 -g -DWIN32 -DNDEBUG -D_WINDOWS -D_MBCS -D_USRDLL

